dc_title_s: France--west coast, entrance to the Gironde, Pointe de la Courbre to Pointe de la Negade (Raster Image)
dc_description_s: Prepared and published by the National Imagery and Mapping Agency. Depths shown by isolines and soundings. Relief shown by contours and spot heights. "From a French chart of 1985." Place names in French with glossary in English. "Copyright 1997 by the United States Government. No copyright claimed under Title 17 U.S.C." "Soundings in meters." Insets: A. Rade de Royan. Scale 1:20,005 -- B. Port du Verdon. Scale 1:20,040. Includes tables of tidal currents and tide heights. Map no.37403. This map is part of a collection of scanned and georeferenced nautical charts produced by the National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency (NGA).
dc_creator_sm: United States. National Imagery and Mapping Agency
